Note Frequencies

A quick reference for musical notes and their corresponding frequencies and wavelengths.
Reference
Published

April 7, 2024

I’ve had Bryan Suits’ website bookmarked for years specifically for the page on converting musical notes to frequencies and wavelengths. I have learned that he has sadly passed away recently, and Michigan Tech removed his website in the process. This is a recreation of the table on his website, mostly so I can access it again more easily.

Frequencies for equal-tempered scale

Speed of Sound = 345 m/s = 1130 ft/s = 770 miles/hr. To convert lengths in cm to inches, divide by 2.54.

Select a frequency for A4 below. “Middle C” is C4.
